<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>React app</title>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/react@16/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@16/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/babel-standalone@6.15.0/babel.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="mydiv">
    Hello React
  </div>
  <script type="text/babel">
    function Test() {
      const akash = () => console.log("test");
      return <button onClick={akash}>Click me</button>;
    }
    
    class Hello extends React.Component {
      render() {
        return (
          <div>
            Hello React with code <Test />
          </div>
        );
      }
    }
    
    ReactDOM.render(<Hello />, document.getElementById("mydiv"));
  </script>
</body>
</html>
this is code for reactjs without using npm or any instalation of nodejs . This is helpful for many beginners.
